Voice onset time data from three populations.

Source: R/vot.R
vot.Rd

A dataset containing raw voice onset time (VOT) data in ms from three groups. This data was simulated in R based off the data set used in Casillas, Diaz, & Simonet (2015).

Casillas, J. V., Diaz, Y. and Simonet, M. (2015). "Acoustics of Spanish and English coronal stops". In ICPhS 18. Ed. by T. S. C. for ICPhS 2015. Proceedings of the 18th International Congress of Phonetic Sciences. University of Glasgow: Glasgow. http://www.icphs2015.info, ISSN: 241-0669, pp. 1-5.

vot

Format

A data frame with 720 rows and 5 variables:

participant

subject id labels

language

language spoken, spanish/english

item

target word

repetition

iteration of item

vot

vot values, in ms

Source

https://github.com/jvcasillas/untidydata
